GUID.desc: ESRI GUID to be used in merging related tables

CASE_ID.desc: Unique identifier of the crash case

CID.desc: Unique identifier of the crash case

PID.desc: Unique identifier for the party case

VID.desc: Unique identifier of the victim case

PARTY_NUMBER.desc: A number that together with the CASE_ID uniquely identifies a party in a crash

VICTIM_NUMBER.desc: The unique identifier of the victim

CRASHES_INDICATOR.desc: Binary flag, 1 if the record is a crash, 0 if not

PARTIES_INDICATOR.desc: Binary flag, 1 if the record is a party, 0 if not

VICTIMS_INDICATOR.desc: Binary flag, 1 if the record is a victim, 0 if not

COLLISION_DATETIME.desc: Full date and time string of the crash

COLLISION_DATE.desc: The date when the crash occurred

COLLISION_TIME.desc: The time when the crash occurred in 24h format

ACCIDENT_YEAR.desc: The year when the crash occurred

DAY_OF_WEEK.desc: Code for the day of the week when the crash occurred

PROC_DATE.desc: The date that the crash case was last changed

COLLISION_TIME_RUSH_HOURS.desc: Rush hours interval ranges (Mon-Fri mornings and evenings)

COLLISION_SEVERITY.desc: The worst injury suffered by any victim in the crash

domain.0: No injury, aka property damage only or PDO
domain.2: Suspected serious injury or severe injury
domain.3: Suspected minor injury or visible injury
domain.4: Possible injury or complaint of pain

COLLISION_SEVERITY_BINARY.desc: Binary classification of the worst injury suffered by any victim in the crash

domain.0: Minor (minor injury, pain, or no injury)

COLLISION_SEVERITY_RECLASS.desc: Reclassified crash severity based on the worst injury suffered by any victim in the crash

COLLISION_SEVERITY_RANKED.desc: Ranked crash severity based on the worst injury suffered by any victim in the crash

PARTY_COUNT.desc: Number of parties involved in the crash

VICTIM_COUNT.desc: Number of victims involved in each party

COUNT_SEVERE_INJ.desc: Number of victims in the crash with suspected serous injury or severe injury

COUNT_VISIBLE_INJ.desc: Number of victims in the crash with suspected minor injury or visible injury

COUNT_COMPLAINT_PAIN.desc: Number of victims in the crash with possible injury or complaint of pain

PRIMARY_COLL_FACTOR.desc: The primary cause of the crash

TYPE_OF_COLLISION.desc: The general type of crash as determined by the first injury or damage-causing event

PEDESTRIAN_ACCIDENT.desc: Indicates whether the crash involved a pedestrian

BICYCLE_ACCIDENT.desc: Indicates whether the crash involved a bicycle

MOTORCYCLE_ACCIDENT.desc: Indicates whether the crash involved a motorcycle

TRUCK_ACCIDENT.desc: Indicates whether the crash involved a big truck

HIT_AND_RUN.desc: A flag to indicate the severity of hit-and-run crash. Felony hit-and-run resulted in injury or death to other parties. Misdemeanor hit-and-run did not result in injury or death to other parties

ALCOHOL_INVOLVED.desc: Indicates whether the crash involved a party that had been drinking. Note - a passenger does not count as a party

JURIS.desc: Law enforcement agency that has jurisdiction over the crash

OFFICER_ID.desc: The badge number of the officer who wrote the crash report

REPORTING_DISTRICT.desc: Reporting District on the crash report

CHP_SHIFT.desc: CHP shift at the time of the crash

CNTY_CITY_LOC.desc: The city or unincorporated county where the crash occurred

SPECIAL_COND.desc: A computed value. O means not private property

domain.5: Vista Point or Rest Area or Sales or Inspection Facility

BEAT_TYPE.desc: Location of crash based on beat

domain.7: Vista Point or Rest Area or Scales or Inspection Facility

CHP_BEAT_TYPE.desc: Location of crash based on beat

CHP_BEAT_CLASS.desc: Location of crash based on beat

BEAT_NUMBER.desc: Beat of the officer who reported the crash

PRIMARY_RD.desc: The name of the roadway on which the crash occurred

SECONDARY_RD.desc: The name of the roadway that intersects the primary roadway

DISTANCE.desc: Distance of the crash from the intersection with the secondary roadway in ft

DIRECTION.desc: Direction of the crash from the intersection with the secondary roadway

INTERSECTION.desc: A flag that denotes if the crash occurred at the intersection with the secondary roadway

WEATHER_1.desc: Weather condition at the time of the crash

WEATHER_2.desc: Additional weather condition at the time of the crash

WEATHER_COMBINED.desc: Combined Weather Conditions from WEATHER_1 and WEATHER_2 fields in numeric codes by weather conditions severity

ROAD_SURFACE.desc: Roadway surface condition at the time of the crash in the traffic lane(s) involved

ROAD_COND_1.desc: Roadway condition at the time of the crash in the traffic lane(s) involved

ROAD_COND_2.desc: Second roadway condition at the time of the crash in the traffic lane(s) involved

LIGHTING.desc: Lighting conditions at the crash location and the time of the crash

CONTROL_DEVICE.desc: Presence and condition of crash related traffic control devices at the time of the crash. Control devices include regulatory, warning, and construction sings. This excludes striping and officers or other persons directing traffic

STATE_HWY_IND.desc: A flag to indicate whether the crash is on or near a state highway

SIDE_OF_HWY.desc: Code provided by Caltrans Coders, applies to divided highway, based on nominal direction of route, for single vehicle is same as nominal direction of travel, overruled by impact with second vehicle after crossing median

TOW_AWAY.desc: A flag to indicate whether the vehicle was towed away from the crash scene

PCF_CODE_OF_VIOL.desc: The law code that was violated and was the primary cause of the crash

PCF_VIOL_CATEGORY.desc: A value computed from the law section that was given as the primary cause of the crash

domain.1: Driving or Bicycling Under the Influence of Alcohol or Drug
domain.23: Pedestrian or Other Under the Influence of Alcohol or Drug

PCF_VIOLATION.desc: The law section given as the primary cause of the crash. The subsection is in the data element pcf_viol_subsection

PCF_VIOL_SUBSECTION.desc: The subsection of the law section given as the primary cause of the crash in the data element pcf_violation

MVIW.desc: Describes what, in conjunction with a motor vehicle in-transport, produced the first injury or damage-causing event, on or off the road

domain.2: Other Motor Vehicle and Additional Object
domain.3: Motor Vehicle on Other Roadway and Additional Object
domain.4: Parked Motor Vehicle and Additional Object

PED_ACTION.desc: The action just prior to the crash of the first pedestrian injured or otherwise involved

domain.C: Crossing in Crosswalk Not at Intersection

NOT_PRIVATE_PROPERTY.desc: Y indicates that the crash did not occur on private property

STWD_VEHTYPE_AT_FAULT.desc: Indicates the Statewide Vehicle Type of the party who is at fault

domain.E: Pickup or panel truck with trailer
domain.G: Truck or truck tractor with trailer

CHP_VEHTYPE_AT_FAULT.desc: Indicates the CHP Vehicle Type of the party whi is at fault

domain.1: Passenger, car, station Wagon, or Jeep
domain.39: Three trailers (includes semi and two trailers)
domain.40: Semi 48 or less with king pin to trailer axle of over 38
domain.45: Highway construction equipment (only while not in construction area)
domain.48: CHP, police, or sheriff car (emergency service or not)
domain.49: CHP, police, or sheriff motorcycle (emergency service or not)
domain.52: Federally legal double cargo combo over 75ft
domain.61: School pupil activity bus I (prior to 2002)
domain.62: School pupil activity bus II (prior to 2002)
domain.72: Pickups and panels - hazardous materials only
domain.73: Pickups and campers - hazardous materials only
domain.77: Three or more axle truck - hazardous materials only
domain.78: Two-axle tank truck - hazardous materials only
domain.79: Three axle tank truck - hazardous materials only
domain.81: Passenger car - hazardous waste or waste-material combo
domain.82: Pickups and panels - hazardous waste or waste-material combo
domain.83: Pickups and campers - hazardous waste or waste-material combo
domain.85: Truck tractor - hazardous waste or waste-material combo
domain.86: Two-axle truck - hazardous waste or waste-material combo
domain.87: Three or more axle truck - hazardous waste or waste-material combo
domain.88: Two-axle tank truck - hazardous waste or waste-material combo
domain.89: Three-axle tank truck - hazardous waste or waste-material combo
domain.95: Miscellaneous non-motorized vehicle (ridden animal, animal-drawn conveyance, train or building) with victim
domain.98: Emergency vehicle on an emergency run
domain.99: Not stated or unknown (hit and run)

PRIMARY_RAMP.desc: A description of the ramp, if any, on primary roadway. This value is computed by the key operator from information on the crash report

SECONDARY_RAMP.desc: A description of the ramp, if any, on secondary roadway. This value is computed by the key operator from information on the crash report

AT_FAULT.desc: Indicates whether the party was at fault in the crash

PARTY_AGE.desc: The age of the party at the time of the crash

RACE.desc: The party's race based on the reporting officer's judgment

PARTY_NUMBER_KILLED.desc: Number of killed victims in the party

PARTY_NUMBER_INJURED.desc: Number of injured victims in the party

PARTY_SOBRIETY.desc: The state of sobriety of the party

domain.C: Had been drinking, not under influence

PARTY_DRUG_PHYSICAL.desc: The state of the party with regard to drugs and physical condition

DIR_OF_TRAVEL.desc: Direction that the party was traveling at the time of the crash. The direction is the direction of the highway, not the compass direction

PARTY_SAFETY_EQUIP_1.desc: The safety equipment of the party

domain.R: Child restraint in vehicle not used
domain.S: Child restraint in vehicle, use unknown
domain.T: Child restraint in vehicle, improper use

PARTY_SAFETY_EQUIP_2.desc: The safety equipment of the party

domain.R: Child restraint in vehicle not used
domain.S: Child restraint in vehicle, use unknown
domain.T: Child restraint in vehicle, improper use

domain.O: Not applicable (used for parked cars, bicyclists, pedestrians, and party type others)
domain.E: Used if the officer is called away from the scene of the crash prior to obtaining the insurance information

SP_INFO_1.desc: Value A indicates that the crash involved in a vehicle known to be, or believed to be, transporting a hazardous material as defined in CVC Section 353, whether or not the crash involved a hazardous material incident

SP_INFO_3.desc: Value E indicates that the crash involved a motor vehicle in-transport passing a stopped school bus with its red signal lamps in operation pursuant to CVC Section 22112, or reacting to, pursuant to CVC Section 22454

OAF_VIOLATION_CODE.desc: Other associated factor law code violated

OAF_VIOL_CAT.desc: Category of the factor that contributed to the crash but was not the primary cause of the crash

domain.20: Driving or bicycling under the influence of alcohol or drug

OAF_VIOL_SECTION.desc: The CVC section of the secondary violation that contributed to the crash

OAF_VIOLATION_SUFFIX.desc: the subsection of the CVC section of the secondary violation that contributed to the crash

OAF_1.desc: A factor that contributed to the crash but was not the primary cause of the crash

OAF_2.desc: A factor that contributed to the crash but was not the primary cause of the crash

MOVE_PRE_ACC.desc: The action of the vehicle prior to the crash and before evasive action. This movement does not have to correspond with the PCF

VEHICLE_YEAR.desc: The model year of the party's vehicle

VEHICLE_MAKE.desc: The make of the party's vehicle

STWD_VEHICLE_TYPE.desc: Type of the party's vehicle according to a list called statewide vehicle type

domain.E: Pickup or panel truck with trailer
domain.G: Truck or truck tractor with trailer

SPECIAL_INFO_F.desc: The value F indicate that the party's vehicle is a 75ft motor truck combo

SPECIAL_INFO_G.desc: The value G indicates that the party's vehicle is a 32ft trailer combo

domain.2: Passenger (includes non-operator on bicycle or any victim on/in parked vehicle or multiple victims on/in non-motor vehicle)

VICTIM_AGE.desc: The age of the victim at the time of the crash

VICTIM_DEGREE_OF_INJURY.desc: The severity of the injury to the victim

VICTIM_DEGREE_OF_INJURY_BINARY.desc: Binary classification of the severity of the injury to the victim

domain.0: Minor (minor injury, pain, or no injury)

VICTIM_SEATING_POSITION.desc: The seating position of the victim

domain.8: Rear occupant of truck or van

VICTIM_SAFETY_EQUIP_1.desc: The safety equipment of the victim

domain.R: Child restraint in vehicle not used
domain.S: Child restraint in vehicle, use unknown
domain.T: Child restraint in vehicle, improper use

VICTIM_SAFETY_EQUIP_2.desc: The safety equipment of the victim

domain.R: Child restraint in vehicle not used
domain.S: Child restraint in vehicle, use unknown
domain.T: Child restraint in vehicle, improper use

VICTIM_EJECTED.desc: Indicates whether the victim was ejected from the vehicle

CITY_POPDENS.desc: City population density, population per square mile

CITY_HUDENS.desc: City housing density, houses per square mile

CITY_POPT.desc: Total population in the city's area

CITY_HUT.desc: Total housing units in the city's area

CITY_POPA.desc: Total Asian population in the city's area

CITY_POPB.desc: Total Black or African American population in the city's area

CITY_POPH.desc: Total Hispanic population in the city's area

CITY_POPW.desc: Total White population in the city's area

CITY_VEHICLES.alias: City Aggregate Number of Vehicles Commuting
CITY_VEHICLES.desc: Aggregate number of vehicles used in commuting in the city's area

CITY_TRAVEL_TIME.alias: City Aggregate Travel Time to Work (min)
CITY_TRAVEL_TIME.desc: Aggregate travel time to work (in minutes) in the city's area

RID.desc: Road ID matching from the road's layer

RNAME.desc: Road name from the OC Tiger/Lines layer

RCAT.desc: Road category from the OC Tiger/Lines layer

RLENGTH.desc: Road length from the OC Tiger/Lines layer

LATITUDE.desc: Latitude of the crash location in decimal degrees. The decimal point is included. LATITUDE and LONGITUDE are from the crash report

LONGITUDE.desc: Longitude of the crash location in decimal degrees. The decimal point is included. There is no minus sign. The longitude is understood to be West of Meridian. LATITUDE and LONGITUDE are from the crash report

POINT_X.desc: The longitude of the geocoded location, uses the World Geodetic System from 1984 (WGS84). POINT_X and POINT_Y are generated using the geociding process by UC Berkeley Safe TREC

POINT_Y.desc: The latitude of the geocoded location, uses the World Geodetic System from 1984 (WGS84). POINT_X and POINT_Y are generated using the geociding process by UC Berkeley Safe TREC
